  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Add your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are crispy and cooked through – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670330603265-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670330603265-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670330603265-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670330603265-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670330603265-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain your <strong>tofu </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper, then slice the <strong>tofu</strong> into 2 pieces per person</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced tofu </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then set aside for later – this is your<strong> mustard marinated tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670330606868-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
